tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE fashion_photography (
  image_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
  shoot_date DATE,
  model_name VARCHAR(50),
  clothing_brand VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE image_catalog (
    image_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    image_url TEXT NOT NULL,
    shoot_date DATE NOT NULL,
    model_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    brand_name TEXT NOT NULL
);

CREATE TABLE model_info (
    model_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name TEXT NOT NULL,
    height INT,
    weight INT,
    age INT,
    agency TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE fashion_images (
    image_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    image_url VARCHAR(255),
    shoot_date DATE,
    model_name VARCHAR(50),
    brand_name VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE models (
    model_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_name VARCHAR(50),
    gender VARCHAR(10),
    nationality VARCHAR(50)
)

CREATE TABLE brands (
    brand_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    brand_name VARCHAR(50),
    established_year INT,
    headquarters_location VARCHAR(100)
)

CREATE TABLE shoots (
    shoot_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    shoot_date DATE,
    location VARCHAR(100),
    photographer VARCHAR(50),
    notes TEXT
)
CREATE TABLE Image (image_id INT PRIMARY KEY, image_url VARCHAR(255), shoot_date DATE, model_name VARCHAR(50), brand_name VARCHAR(50));
CREATE TABLE Model (model_id INT PRIMARY KEY, model_name VARCHAR(50), date_of_birth DATE, nationality VARCHAR(50));
CREATE TABLE Brand (brand_id INT PRIMARY KEY, brand_name VARCHAR(50), country_origin VARCHAR(50));
CREATE TABLE ImageModelRelation (image_id INT, model_id INT, PRIMARY KEY(image_id, model_id));
CREATE TABLE ImageBrandRelation (image_id INT, brand_id INT, PRIMARY KEY(image_id, brand_id));
